### Test Simplified Enumeration Endpoints

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5214/api

### Get Document Status Enumeration (Names and Ordinals)
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents/search/enums/document-status
Accept: application/json

###

### Get Search Methods Enumeration (Names and Ordinals)
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents/search/enums/search-methods
Accept: application/json

###

### Get Document Retrieval Options Enumeration (Names and Ordinals)
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents/search/enums/retrieval-options
Accept: application/json

###

### Get Keyword Data Types Enumeration (Names and Ordinals)
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents/search/enums/keyword-data-types
Accept: application/json

###

### Get Search Operators Enumeration (Names and Ordinals)
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents/search/enums/search-operators
Accept: application/json

###

### Example: Using Ordinal Values in Search
### Search using DocumentStatus ordinal value (0 = Active)
GET {{baseUrl}}/documents?documentType=Contract&status=0&maxResults=10
Accept: application/json

###

### Example: Advanced Search with Ordinal Values
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "SearchMethod": 1,
  "DocumentType": "Legal Contract",
  "Status": 0,
  "RetrievalOptions": 1,
  "MaxResults": 20
}

###

### Example: Custom Query Search with Ordinal Data Types and Operators
POST {{baseUrl}}/documents/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "SearchMethod": 2,
  "CustomQueryName": "ContractSearch",
  "Keywords": [
    {
      "Name": "ContractValue",
      "DataType": 1,
      "Value": 50000,
      "Operator": 2
    },
    {
      "Name": "Department",
      "DataType": 0,
      "Value": "Legal",
      "Operator": 0
    },
    {
      "Name": "ExpiryDate",
      "DataType": 3,
      "Value": "2026-12-31",
      "Operator": 5
    }
  ],
  "Status": 0,
  "MaxResults": 25
}

###